2026-07-08T09:41Z HDMX-coding-agent note Follow-up filed: tickets/0183 (add the null-model sentence to A.5). 0152 rows E3c/E3d/R1.2 stay as-signed (FORTIFIED supports them; no reopen).
2026-07-08T13:05Z HDMX-coding-agent note Red-team circularity fix (PR #876). The 09:39 run derived the three seed-sets from Louvain communities detected on the SAME graph the null then tests; Louvain maximises modularity by construction, so that run overstates the evidence for the HISTORICAL three-tradition claim. Added a second, non-circular labelling: a-priori anchors fixed from @tbl-traditions authors (config pre2007_separation.anchor_authors), assigned by first-author match with NO community detection in the labelling path (label_nodes_by_anchors). Both labellings now ship in one output with a `labelling` column.
2026-07-08T13:06Z HDMX-coding-agent note Dual run (tab_null_separation_pre2007.csv, degree-preserving double_edge_swap, N=1000, seed=42, n_truncated=0 on all four tests — no partial mixing). louvain_anchored (84 nodes / 369 edges): within_tradition_share obs 0.8889 vs null 0.3736+-0.0202 z=25.50 p=0.000999; modularity obs 0.5542 vs null -0.0123+-0.0202 z=28.04 p=0.000999. a_priori_anchors (16 anchor-author nodes / 33 edges): within_tradition_share obs 0.8485 vs null 0.6077+-0.0334 z=7.21 p=0.000999; modularity obs 0.1693 vs null -0.0373+-0.0334 z=6.19 p=0.000999.
2026-07-08T13:07Z HDMX-coding-agent verdict FORTIFIED holds. Threshold judged by: z>3 AND empirical p<0.01 on BOTH statistics (the exit-criterion bar). The non-circular a-priori-anchors run clears it (z=7.21 and 6.19; p=0.000999 = the N=1000 floor, no null replicate reached the observed value). The effect is markedly weaker than the Louvain-anchored run (z~6-7 vs z~26; modularity 0.17 vs 0.55) — expected, since the a-priori seed-sets are only the ~16 named-author works, a thinner and harder test, and the sparser subgraph gives the null a higher baseline (share 0.61 vs 0.37). It still beats the density-conditioned null convincingly on both statistics with zero community detection in the labelling path, so the pre-2007 separation is a real historically-defined boundary, not an artefact of modularity maximisation on the tested graph. A.5 must lead with the a-priori result, not the z~26 Louvain figure.
2026-07-08T13:08Z HDMX-coding-agent note Two panel considers landed in the same pass: (a) double_edge_swap now returns a truncation flag; null_separation_test counts n_truncated (in the CSV) and logs the requested swap count + warns on any truncation — no silently partial rewiring. (b) Single source of truth for the cutoff year: plot_fig_traditions.py no longer hardcodes CUTOFF_YEAR=2006; both it and compute_pre2007_coverage.py read pipeline_loaders.pre2007_cutoff_year(cfg) (= periodization break[0]-1). Adjusted 0183 planned A.5 wording to the a-priori numbers.

--- body ---
## Context
The Act-I corpus evidence claims the three traditions (environmental
economics, development economics, burden-sharing) were structurally
separate before 2007 (manuscript A.1 question 2 / A.5; 0152 rows E3c,
E3d, R1.2 — author-signed). Author diagnosis (2026-07-08): the pre-2007
citation graph is the sparsest slice of the corpus (retro-indexing skew,
ticket 0071; grey literature under-referenced), so co-citation would
show separation almost regardless — a falsificationist test with low
power is not a test. Decision: **fortify** — measure whether the
observed separation exceeds what sparsity alone produces; **demote with
evidence** if it does not. Related, complementary, stays open: 0077
(per-year density vs G2/G9 breaks). See also 0074 (Louvain seed
variance), 0076 (joint type-I error).

## Relevant files
- `scripts/compute_null_model.py` + `scripts/_permutation_accel.py` — existing permutation-null machinery (G9_community pattern to reuse)
- `scripts/pipeline_loaders.py` — corpus access ONLY through loaders (arch rule 9): `load_refined_citations()`, `load_refined_works()`
- `config/analysis.yaml` — seeds, window bounds, permutation count (no hardcoded constants; arch rules 6–7)
- `content/manuscript.qmd` — A.1 tripod + A.5; the claims at stake (do NOT edit in this ticket)
- `tickets/0152-…` rows E3c/E3d/R1.2 — signed responses whose support depends on the verdict
- `docs/reimport-inventory-v205.md` — B19/B05 context

## Actions
1. **Diagnostic** (decides interpretive regime): for the pre-2007 slice —
   work count, share with ≥1 outgoing edge in `refined_citations`, median
   references per work, coverage split academic vs grey. One CSV +
   schema (`content/tables/tab_pre2007_coverage.csv`).
2. **Null model**: degree-preserving rewiring (configuration model) of
   the pre-2007 co-citation graph, N permutations (seed + N from
   config/analysis.yaml). Statistic: separation of the three tradition
   seed-sets (inter-tradition co-citation share, and modularity of the
   3-partition as secondary). Observed vs null → z / empirical p.
   One CSV output per Phase 2 rules (1 invocation = 1 output).
3. **Verdict artifact**: short note (path referenced from this ticket's
   log at close) stating FORTIFIED (observed separation exceeds the
   sparsity-conditioned null) or DEMOTE (it does not), with the numbers.
4. **File the follow-up manuscript ticket** per verdict (one validation
   unit, do not edit the manuscript here): FORTIFIED → add the null-model
   sentence to A.5; DEMOTE → reword the A.1 tripod (two tests + one
   descriptive consistency check) and reopen 0152 rows E3c/E3d for
   author re-sign.

## Test
- `tests/test_null_separation.py::test_three_cliques_beat_rewired_null` —
  toy graph with three cliques must yield observed separation ≫ null;
  a random graph of same degree sequence must not. Red first (TDD).

## Verification
- [x] Scripts follow Phase 2 rules: `--output` via script_io_args, Pandera
      schema, seed from config, loaders only, save path from Makefile `$@`
- [x] New `.mk` include or existing divergence.mk extension — no 400-line
      Makefile edits
- [x] `make check-fast` green

## Invariants
- No Phase 1 trigger (works from the existing contract files)
- `content/manuscript.qmd` untouched by this ticket
- 0152 rows untouched until the follow-up ticket

## Exit criteria
- [x] Coverage diagnostic archived with schema (compute_pre2007_coverage.py + Pre2007CoverageSchema; regenerate via `make pre2007-coverage`)
- [x] Null run archived (seed, N, statistic) — numbers traceable per the provenance norm (compute_null_separation.py + NullSeparationSchema; `make pre2007-separation`, seed/N in config/analysis.yaml). Dual labelling: louvain_anchored (comparison) + a_priori_anchors (non-circular, load-bearing); `labelling` + `n_truncated` columns in the output
- [x] Verdict FORTIFIED/DEMOTE stated in ticket log with the deciding numbers (FORTIFIED, see log 2026-07-08T09:40Z)
- [x] Follow-up manuscript-wording ticket filed per verdict (tickets/0183)
